joseph and kansas city mo as president of nfo a denverbased 
organization which represents more than 250000 farm families 
staley often lobbied congress on farm legislation and related 
issues 
in 1986 staley finished third in the democratic primary for the 
us senate in missouri in november 1986 he filed for chapter 11 
bankruptcy saying his 956acre farm was unprofitable and that 
personal loans he took out to cover costs of his senate bid had 
worsened his financial problems 
