how hard are sat questions 
here are questions from a test administered on may 2 1987 
reprinted by permission of the educational testing service which 
is the copyright owner of the questions included is the percentage 
of testtakers correctly answering each 
 
math 
 
if a b and c are integers the expression ab c is always 
equal to each of the following except 
a a bc 
b ac b 
c c ba 
d ab ac 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
answer is a correctly answered by 79 percent of testtakers 
 
if the average arithmetic mean of six numbers is 6 and the 
sum of four of the numbers is 20 what is the average of the other 
two numbers 
a 7 
b 8 
c 8 
d 28 
e 32 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
answer is d correctly answered by 16 percent of testtakers 
 
verbal 
 
directions choose the word most nearly the opposite in meaning 
to the words in capital letters 
 
uncork 
a reform 
b empty 
c seal 
d dry out 
e blend in 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
answer is c correctly answered by 95 percent of testtakers 
 
magnanimous 
a dainty 
b latent 
c vengeful 
d conspicuous 
e compatible 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
answer is c correctly answered by 11 percent of testtakers 
</TEXT>
