<TEXT>
american greg louganis won his second 
consecutive olympic gold medal in mens springboard diving tuesday 
just a day after he hit the back of his head on the board 
sporting a bare spot on his head louganis gave a picturesque 
performance and knocked off two chinese challengers 
he finished with 73080 tan liangde of china runnerup to 
louganis at the 1984 summer games had 70488 to win the silver 
medal and li deliang of china finished with 66528 to take the 
bronze 
the other american mark bradshaw came in fifth with 65299 
behind albin killat of west germany who had 66147 points 
the dive that marred louganis performance in mondays 
preliminaries caused him no problem tuesday the reverse 
2somersault in the pike position earned three 9s three 85s and 
one 8 in the preliminaries he received two zeros one 5 three 
1s one 15 and five stitches 
louganis 28 is seeking to become the first man to win both the 
springboard and platform events in consecutive olympics he 
captured his first olympic medal in 1976 when at the age of 16 he 
finished second in the platform competition 
