allowing county hospital patients to refuse to be treated by people 
with the aids virus but the hospital has not developed a way to 
make the policy work 
the county board which also serves as the hospital board of 
directors voted 152 monday to adopt the policy that would make 
the hospital the first in the nation to give patients that right 
officials said 
our reaction is one of dismay dr lonnie bristow a trustee 
of the american medical association said last week after the 
boards health and hospital committee approved the policy 
there has been no case in this country of a patient 
contracting the aids virus from a healthcare worker bristow 
said 
