appealing for dialogue between the two sides 
saw maung overthrew maung maung who took over aug 19 as 
burmas first civilian leader since the 1962 military coup maung 
maung had ended martial law and withdrawn soldiers from the streets 
as a concession to protesters but the opposition demanded that he 
allow an interim government conduct the democratic elections he had 
promised 
