burma socialist program party the target of months of widespread 
street protests protesters blame the countrys sole legal party 
for 26 years of repression and economic ruin 
burma has been in turmoil since students rioted last september 
against government economic policies security forces killed scores 
of protesters in march and june and demonstrations since july have 
forced the resignations of longtime strongman ne win and his 
successor sein lwin who lasted 17 days at least 112 people died 
in the rioting against sein lwin 
