the security council unanimously voted 
today to approve an independence referendum for western sahara 
where marxist guerrillas haven been battling moroccos occupation 
forces for 13 years 
the 150 security council vote approved the appointment of a 
special representative of the secretarygeneral to monitor a 
referendum that would result in western saharas independence or 
affiliation with morocco 
secretarygeneral javier perez de cuellar reminded the members 
of the council that on aug 30 representatives of the polisario 
independence movement and morocco met with him in geneva to approve 
the referendum and peace plan with certain reservations 
the proposals aimed at the restoration of peace in the region 
provide a framework for the conclusion of a ceasefire and the 
establishment of conditions necessary for the organization of a 
credible referendum said the un chief 
the referendum will be organized and monitored by the united 
nations in cooperation with the organization of african unity he 
said the organization has played a major role in arranging the 
dialogue between polisario and morocco 
perez de cuellar said a special representative from his office 
a civilian unit a military unit and a security unit would work for 
peace in the area 
the proposals also provide that the kingdom of morocco will 
carry out an appropriate substantial and gradual reduction of its 
troops in the western sahra with remaining soldiers to be 
barracked under the supervision of un military observers 
polisarios fighters would also be quartered under un 
supervision 
the marxistled polisario movement of about 8000 fighters has 
been battling for the independence of western sahara since spains 
colonial administration withdrew in 197576 and moroccan 
occupation troops took over the phosphaterich desert territory in 
northwest africa 
more than 10000 people have died in the nearly 13yearold 
guerrilla war which has cost morocco up to 2 million a day to 
fight 
western sahara covers about 110000 square miles its population 
was set at 76000 in 1974 during the last spanish colonial census 
under the un plan only people born in the territory may vote 
in the referendum 
determining who is eligible will be a major chore for the 
referendum monitors polisario claims about 165000 eligible 
western saharans live in its refugee camps near tindouf in algeria 
which funds and shelters polisario but morocco says they are not 
eligible 
morocco claims that 90 percent of the 150000 residents of 
moroccanoccupied sections of western sahara are eligible but 
polisario says twothirds of them are moroccan immigrants 
