breuning be barred from working as a research psychologist for 10 
years and that he make 20000 restitution to his former employer 
the university of pittsburgh which has repaid the federal 
institute more than 163000 
they also agreed to drop a charge that breuning obstructed the 
institutes investigation of his datas authenticity 
breuning claimed to have done the research while working at a 
psychiatric clinic affiliated with the universitys medical school 
from 1982 to 1984 but while he claimed that 99 patients 
participated in the studies only 25 students received the drugs 
according to e thomas roberts an assistant us attorney 
us district judge frank a kaufman set sentencing for nov 10 
the maximum possible sentence is 10 years in prison and 20000 in 
fines breuning remains free on bond 
according to the mental health institute breuning had a 
significant impact in the field of drug therapies for hyperactive 
retarded children finding that stimulants such as ritalin and 
dexedrine helped control such children with fewer adverse side 
effects than the tranquilizers previously used 
