<TEXT>
interest rates on shortterm treasury 
securities fell in the governments latest auction 
the treasury department sold 70 billion in threemonth bills 
at an average discount rate of 717 percent on monday down from 
721 percent last week another 70 billion was sold in sixmonth 
bills at an average discount rate of 734 percent down from 741 
percent last week 
the rates were the lowest since threemonth bills sold for 705 
percent on aug 15 and sixmonth bills averaged 726 on aug 8 
the new discount rates understate the actual return to investors 
740 percent for threemonth bills with a 10000 bill selling 
for 981880 and and 773 percent for sixmonth bills selling for 
