<TEXT>
unless the financial industry takes a 
real interest in a new form of farm lending the opportunity may 
not arise again an investment firm executive told a forum of 
midwestern bankers tuesday 
jeff rodman said the newly created federal agricultural mortgage 
corp known as farmer mac could help banks keep rural customers 
and reduce the risk of writing farm loans farmers meantime are 
hoping the agency will spur competition for farm loans and hold 
down interest rates 
rodman said that despite high hopes for farmer mac there are 
many unanswered questions about the agency designed to establish a 
secondary market for farm loans one big unknown is how much of a 
demand exists for such new markets 
if farmer mac does not sell well im afraid its an 
opportunity we may not get again he told a seminar at the iowa 
bankers association convention 
farmer mac was established by congress to enable rural lenders 
such as banks insurance companies and the farm credit system to 
combine loans and use those pools of mortgages as security for 
investments sold to the public it is still in the process of being 
organized and is months away from adopting even such basic 
regulations as how its loan pools will be organized 
rodman is vice president for marketing for mabsco capital inc 
a des moinesbased company designed to provide banks access to 
secondary markets mabsco is owned by the insurance company mutual 
of new york and state banking associations in iowa and 11 other 
states rodman said his company is interested in becoming one of 
the organizations pooling farm loans and selling mortgagebacked 
securities to investors 
about 8 billion in new farm mortgage credit is extended every 
year and only part of that will qualify for farmer mac securities 
according to the federal reserve bank of kansas city mo that will 
make farmer mac a small country cousin to such providers of 
secondary residential mortgages as ginnie mae freddie mac and 
fannie mae 
the outstanding principal balances of residential mortgages 
backing securities guaranteed by those three established agencies 
formally known as the government national mortgage association 
federal home loan mortgage corp and federal national mortgage 
association totaled more than 670 billion at the end of last 
year according to the kansas city fed 
whats more farm loan demand has been in the doldrums in recent 
months 
following the farm crisis of the first half of the 1980s in 
which farm debt rose to record levels bringing down many banks 
survivors began staging a recovery assisted by huge government 
subsidies as a result many surviving agricultural and rural banks 
are flush with cash 
but rodman said credit could begin getting tight as early as 
1989 making farmer mac a welcome tool for assuring liquidity and 
enabling lenders to shift the risk of longterm loans to investors 
this summers drought reduced crop yields thinned livestock 
