analysts are predicting loan demand from farmers will be growing as 
they expand plantings next spring not only are farmers expected to 
plant more next year but the price of seed and fertilizer is 
rising and interest rates have been headed higher 
if loan funds get tight we can see demand develop quickly 
to harness farmer mac rodman said 
analysts say yields on farmer mac securities should be 
competitive with fannie mae and other secondary markets for 
mortgages the securities will be backed with a 15 billion line 
of credit at the us treasury that can be tapped if losses in any 
mortgage pool exceed a 10 percent reserve fund established by 
lenders and pool operators 
